This paper deals with traffic analysis attacks on the Tor anonymity system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attacks are based on observing throughput information, which involves network protocols and communication systems (cs.NI). The paper also presents experiments and validation of the attacks, which involves data analysis and statistical methods (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of the attacks on user privacy, which falls under the category of cybercrime and cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
